I didn‚Äôt get a great picture but this is our maintenance director Dewayne Melton fogging the bus after this morning‚Äôs route. He does this to every bus after every route and even halfway through some routes. The kids social distance, wear masks, and we keep the windows down and air circulating. post_text: GO WARRIORS!
shared_text:
Chad Austin is with Kate Mosley and 3 others.
September 1 at 11:09 AM ¬∑

The math department at IHS is hitting on all cylinders (haha get it)? They have totally restructured the whole department. There are kids who choose our math department over engineering classes. There is not any other math department around that can compete! They came to me and said they needed some things in order to do what they wanted to do, about $2500 worth. I told them we would find a way somehow. All of our textbook money was already spent, but we went to work finding money. Thanks to many special people and one business owner who wished to stay anonymous, we were able to get their entire wishlist.

The entire math department now has new doc cameras, web cameras, and new digital books and teaching material! Every kid can download their book 9-12! All of this to go along with the best math teachers in a 100 mile radius! Go Warriors!
#getonthewarriornationtrain #jointhemovementatIHS

View the updated framework here: https://sde.ok.gov/ReturnToLearn

Changes are denoted as either "Updated" or "New" within the document.

Guidance includes:
*Oklahoma School Safety Protocols
*What to do when a staff member or student exhibits symptoms of COVID-19 at school
*What to do when a staff member or student tests positive for COVID-19 or has been in close contact with someone who tests positive
*Guidelines on quarantining of staff members and students
*How schools can assist in contact tracing
*Recommendations for conducting in-person classes in physical education and fine arts
*Recommendations for conducting fire and tornado drills

August 4 at 3:42 PM ¬∑

Kiamichi Tech ‚Äì Idabel campus orientation paperwork pick-up/drop-off details are listed in the post. Appointments are not needed. Packets will be distributed via portico area.
Kiamichi Tech has implemented the Oklahoma State Department of Education Oklahoma School Safety Protocols. In-person classes are suspended until our county infection rate of COVID-19 is reduced to a yellow/low level. The Oklahoma State Department of Health releases weekly trend data that coincides with the color alert level on Fridays. Please refer to our Facebook page for weekly updates regarding our return to school plan as it relates to the county infection rates.
The Kiamichi Tech Return To School Preparedness Plan can be found at https://www.ktc.edu/282166_2.
The Oklahoma State Department of Health COVID-19 Alert System can be found at https://coronavirus.health.ok.gov/covid-19-alert-system.

July 15 at 4:06 PM ¬∑

I know that online schools like Epic are great in some situations for certain students. To each their own. However, I‚Äôd like to encourage parents to consider that most schools are going to offer a virtual option before you decide to enroll elsewhere. Schools are the hearts of their communities. Odds are your small-town, local school has invested in your children. Why not consider riding out this storm together. If massive numbers of students withdraw from our local schools, it will affect our schools and communities. Your administrators, teachers, and staff are working hard to formulate a plan for the unknown. Education will go on. We‚Äôll get through this...hopefully it‚Äôs together.

Idabel Kiwanis
June 2 at 2:06 PM ¬∑

Idabel Kiwanis Club is pleased to announce two scholarship winners for 2020. At today‚Äôs meeting Lily Van Gaal was presented with a check by President/Lt. Governor Frank Acker. This is the first installment of four. She will be attending Southeastern Oklahoma State in the fall to major in occupational health and safety. Her parents Jan Van Gaal and Anja Kramer were on hand to share the moment.

Frank also named Dawson Williston as the recipient of the $500 Rusty Farley Scholarship designated for Haworth students. Dawson was accompanied by his mother, Shonona Webb. Dawson will be attending UCO, where he plans to major in Biology as a foundation for a career in dentistry.

Sincere congratulations to both of these students!

Idabel Middle School Show Choir
May 4 at 8:48 AM ¬∑

Whitney has a beautiful alto voice and a giant personality. She‚Äôs always smiling and is a joy to be around! She worked very hard this year and earned a spot in the Southeastern Oklahoma All District Honor Choir and scored a superior at district solo contest. I‚Äôm so happy that Whitney has another year in our choir! ‚ù§Ô∏è

‚Ä¢

‚ÄúMy name is Whitney, I like that you can have fun in choir. You will want to come and join -TRUST ME!! You get to show your talent and not be ashamed!! You will have a great year and great memories in choir. My favorite memory in choir personally is when we went to contest and we all made superiors so did I, it was AMAZING!! I know I have said this alot but you will not regret trying out and being in that class and showing the inner singer you are. Show that beautiful voice of yours!! You will also love that u will not be judged by anyone. Personally I decided to try out for district choir. I made it but I did not make it to all state but that doesn‚Äôt mean I don‚Äôt have a beautiful voice. I hope you tryout because you will not regret it.üòÅüëçüèª‚Äù

We are featuring our senior members! Up first is Lilly-Anna van Gaal!

Lilly, you are so hardworking and driven! We know you'll go far and achieve whatever you set your mind to. Congratulations on earning your State FFA Degree! We know it took so much work!

Lilly is attending SOSU in Durant after high school. She plans to study Occupational Health and Safety and pursue a doctorate in the same field.
üåü
Lilly's favorite high school memories are leaving school to attend anything agriculture-related, whether skeet shoots, speech contests, or her favorite things: livestock shows!
üåü
Lilly said she doesn't have just one favorite teacher but is grateful to all her teachers who pushed her, even though it might have made her a little mad, to keep going and make good grades. She said they helped her learn and find out what she wants to do after high school.

post_text:
This is the time of year some unscrupulous sales businesses call around and claim they are representing Idabel Public Schools and they are demanding money for t-shirts, balls, calendars, magazines, coozies, clothing, stadium seats, flags, bumper stickers, etc.

No outside solicitors have permission to call on behalf of Idabel Public Schools without written permission from the Superintendent. If anyone calls you or your business on behalf of the school, ask for a copy of this approved letter. If they cannot provide a current signed letter get their information, hangup, and call me. IPS will never send vendors to contact you personally. We handle all of our own solicitations. Please share this information.

Go Warriors!

Hofmeister proposes State Board of Education approve continuous learning for students starting April 6, school buildings to remain closed

Oklahoma State School Boards Association
March 23 at 3:37 PM ¬∑

State Superintendent of Public Instruction Joy Hofmeister announced today that she will propose a Continuous Learning Plan to the State Board of Education this week to complete the school year for Oklahoma students without reopening school buildings during the global pandemic. While the education of schoolchildren will resume with distance learning, there will not be traditional, in-person instruction or extracurricular activities, instead following critical safety guidance from the Centers for Disease Control with regard to social distancing for students, staff and school families.

The Board will hold a special meeting on Wednesday, March 25. Board members will meet virtually

post_text:
Update on Oklahoma State Basketball Playoffs:
At this time all basketball tournaments will proceed as scheduled.

UPDATE: 9:25 a.m.- Thursday, March 12--The OSSAA continues to actively monitor the public health concerns related to COVID-19. Our Staff has been in contact with the Oklahoma Department of Health this morning and based on the updates we have received, we will we proceed with all tournaments being played as scheduled. We do advise players, coaches, officials, contest workers and spectators to practice good hygiene by washing hands thoroughly and frequently; coughing and sneezing into kleenex and then immediately disposing of it are also recommended. If you have a fever or do not feel well, we ask that you not attend any games. Most games will be live-streamed on the NFHSNetwork.com. A link can be found on the homepage of OSSAA.com. Our Staff will continue to work with the State Health Department in monitoring the situation. The health and safety of all Oklahomans is a priority.
text:
Update on Oklahoma State Basketball Playoffs:
At this time all basketball tournaments will proceed as scheduled.

Our Staff has been in contact with the Oklahoma Department of Health this morning and based on the updates we have received, we will we proceed with all tournaments being played as scheduled. We do advise players, coaches, officials, contest workers and spectators to practice good hygiene by washing hands thoroughly and frequently; coughing and sneezing into kleenex and then immediately disposing of it are also recommended. If you have a fever or do not feel well, we ask that you not attend any games. Most games will be live-streamed on the NFHSNetwork.com. A link can be found on the homepage of OSSAA.com. shared_text:
Charla Clements is with Marlin Coffman and 3 others.
March 1 at 12:24 PM ¬∑

I want to take a minute to tell you all about my experience with Virtual Day. I was nervous. My student population enjoys our CBI and Fun Food Friday activities. I wondered would they do it? Could they do it? Would the parents respond well? WELL! It went great! My students and their parents jumped right in! They used the skills we have been learning at school in the real world setting! Even the kids who were out of town at the Basketball games sent in pictures! My kids at home cooked everything from cookies to ramen to fried chicken! My students used the technology they are most familiar with
(and had access to) to fulfill their virtual assignments. I missed them being at school (yes I went to my classroom and worked) but I am so proud to see them taking their skills to the next level!! #digitalnatives #simplythebest #championsforlife #warriornation

Brandon Allen is with Jeff McCarter and 4 others.
February 21 at 10:38 PM ¬∑

Idabel FFA had an awesome day at the McCurtain County Spring Show! Autumn Bolen had the Grand Champion Market Steer and had the Grand and Reserve English Division Heifers. Christian Coffman was the Third Overall Exotic Division heifer and made the sale as well. We have had a good week and numerous awards. In all, Idabel FFA has 2 Sheep (Champion County Breed)1 Goat (4th overall), 1 Steer (GC), and 3 Heifers in the Premium Sale Saturday night! We may not have a large number of animals but the quality is there. Quality over quantity any day if you ask me!!
#warriorpride

shared_text:
The Chickasaw Nation
February 21 at 3:33 PM ¬∑

Chickasaw Nation Nutrition Services is accepting applications for the Summer EBT for Children program. To qualify, your child must be enrolled in a participating school district and receive free or reduced meals at school. Qualifying families will receive approximately $30 of food per child, per month during the three summer months.

Benefits are received on an EBT card that allows families to conveniently purchase healthy food for the summer. This federally funded program is open to both Native and non-Native families.

To view a list of participating school districts and apply, visit Chickasaw.net/SummerEBT or call (844) 256-3467.

Idabel Rotary is sending seven students to the Rotary Youth Leadership Awards program in Athens, TX this weekend. The students will participate in a variety of activities designed to enhance their leadership skills.
Pictured: Jennifer Andrews, RYLA coordinator for Idabel, Idabel High School juniors, Browning Snider, Jake Dawson, Lauren Coursey, Laurel Reesing, Broken Bow High School juniors, Audrey Rocha, and Kyler Wheat, Rotary President Dennis Wilson.
IHS junior, Kaelin Clay is also attending the camp, but will meet the group later because she is participating in the State Superintendent's Advisory Committee in OKC before she can go.

Congratulations to Idabel FFA Show Team members Autumn Bolen and Christian Coffman! Idabel FFA had 5 head at the Big 8 Expo and 4 of them brought home banners. Autumn had the 5th overall heifer and was also Reserve English as well as 4th Ovetall in the English Division. Christian had the 3rd overall Exotic Heifer and a 3rd place shorthorn. In the Steer show Autumn exhibited the champion English steer and was also the Reserve Overall Champion! Congratulations to these kids and families on their accomplishments. Now to get ready for the Spring Show in a few weeks.

shared_text:
Beverly Ann Stuart‚ÄéIdabel JOM Program
December 17, 2019 at 2:44 PM ¬∑

The Native American Club at IHS delivered gifts and good wishes to our residents at Hills Nursing Home and the women‚Äôs shelter here in Idabel this beautiful morning. We were able to provide lotions, plush toys, handmade Christmas Snow Man ornaments and large posters. Our goal was to reach out and be a blessing to those around us that are sometimes forgotten. Some of our students that had worked on this project were not able to go, but Makenzie and Topanga were exceptional representatives of IHS and our Native American Club. Thanks to our students for doing a great job.

post_text: Idabel Public Schools will be hosting the Roland Rangers on Friday night at 7:30 pm. We will honor the memory of Coach Waymon Potts with a moment of silence at the beginning of the game and with memorial stickers on players' helmets. All Roland fans will be given free admission to the game as well. We mourn with our friends from Roland for the loss of their coach, colleague, friend, and family. Our thoughts and prayers for comfort are with you all. Go Rangers! #nextlevel #preparingchampions #GOWARRIORS

November 7, 2019 at 11:55 AM ¬∑
